title: Swami Vivekananda His Life And Legacy
description:
((( scanned pdf )))





By Swami Tapasyananda, 199 Pages, Paperback.

Swami Vivekananda's spiritual and family background, his extraordinary boyhood. His unique relationship with Master and monastic life. His travel to the west for the Parliament of Religion.

His legacy of restoration of national self-respect, his message of fervent patriotism and spirituality as the link between his patriotism and humanism. He was the Acharya of the whole world and his contribution to Vedantic thought and formation of Ramakrishna order and monastic brotherhood.
